[In brief: pandemic and seasonal flu activity across the globe is low,
but activity is increasing in some parts of the Southern Hemisphere,
with significant activity in certain tropical areas. The Southern
Hemisphere is in the midst of its regular flu season and transmission
appears to have recently peaked in South Africa, where most of the
circulating strains were influenza A (H3N2) and influenza B viruses.
In Australia and New Zealand the pace of flu detections has been
steadily increasing over the past few weeks. In Asia the most active
area of pandemic virus transmission is occurring in India, where there
may be a 2nd pandemic H1N1 wave under way. Elsewhere in Southeast
Asia, the pandemic virus is circulating at low levels in a few
countries. - Mod.CP]
